_branch_names_with_jj"},{"short_id":"rqhxpk","created_at":"2026-05-19T11:22:32.000-05:00","title":"Human Bottlenecks","url":"https://borretti.me/article/human-bottlenecks","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"puhsu","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rqhxpk","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rqhxpk/human_bottlenecks"},{"short_id":"maqmo2","created_at":"2026-05-19T10:43:19.000-05:00","title":"How we used Quint to find over 10 bugs in SQLite while hardening Turso","url":"https://turso.tech/blog/how-we-used-quint-to-find-over-10-bugs-in-sqlite","score":12,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"typesanitizer","user_is_author":false,"tags":["databases","formalmethods"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/maqmo2","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/maqmo2/how_we_used_quint_find_over_10_bugs_sqlite"},{"short_id":"n99slp","created_at":"2026-05-19T09:50:58.000-05:00","title":"It’s all in the name","url":"http://plasmasturm.org/log/mythos-claims/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"gerikson","user_is_author":false,"tags":["security","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/n99slp","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/n99slp/it_s_all_name"},{"short_id":"zotppg","created_at":"2026-05-19T09:37:27.000-05:00","title":"Type out the code","url":"https://haskellforall.com/2026/05/type-out-the-code","score":44,"flags":1,"comment_count":3,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"Gabriella439","user_is_author":true,"tags":["programming"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/zotppg","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/zotppg/type_out_code"},{"short_id":"wed6lj","created_at":"2026-05-19T09:29:40.000-05:00","title":"What would you want from a forge?","url":"","score":13,"flags":0,"comment_count":15,"description":"\u003cp\u003e(This is more or less open ended, but sorta directed to users of Jujutsu and other version control systems. However, if you have a workflow with pure Git that isn't covered by many major forges, I'd appreciate hearing them too!)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI'm referring to features related to version control and the presentation/behavior of repositories itself, rather than things like SPA/JS vs server-rendered HTML, etc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThere have been many ideas in this space, such as Tangled, GitHub's stacked PRs, forgefed, etc., but I haven't found a place where people really voice their opinions and discuss on the design itself. While stacked PRs/MRs, alternative collaboration models, etc., are definitely on-topic, I've found almost no discussion on, e.g., the presentation of tags/commits/tree/blobs themselves, which seem to be largely uniform across forges other than minor formatting differences.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"(This is more or less open ended, but sorta directed to users of Jujutsu and other version control systems. However, if you have a workflow with pure Git that isn't covered by many major forges, I'd appreciate hearing them too!)\r\n\r\nI'm referring to features related to version control and the presentation/behavior of repositories itself, rather than things like SPA/JS vs server-rendered HTML, etc.\r\n\r\nThere have been many ideas in this space, such as Tangled, GitHub's stacked PRs, forgefed, etc., but I haven't found a place where people really voice their opinions and discuss on the design itself. While stacked PRs/MRs, alternative collaboration models, etc., are definitely on-topic, I've found almost no discussion on, e.g., the presentation of tags/commits/tree/blobs themselves, which seem to be largely uniform across forges other than minor formatting differences.","submitter_user":"runxiyu","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","design","vcs"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/wed6lj","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/wed6lj/what_would_you_want_from_forge"},{"short_id":"pliqep","created_at":"2026-05-19T09:02:55.000-05:00","title":"Under the Hood: Building a Real-Time Chord Recognizer","url":"https://whatchord.earthmanmuons.com/articles/under-the-hood","score":10,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"soulcutter","user_is_author":false,"tags":["programming"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/pliqep","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/pliqep/under_hood_building_real_time_chord"},{"short_id":"pk139i","created_at":"2026-05-19T08:50:35.000-05:00","title":"The Super Tiny Compiler, but in Ada","url":"https://github.com/tomekw/stcc","score":12,"flags":0,"comment_count":3,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"tomekw","user_is_author":true,"tags":["plt","programming"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/pk139i","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/pk139i/super_tiny_compiler_ada"},{"short_id":"wwcjoc","created_at":"2026-05-19T08:30:09.000-05:00","title":"OpenBSD 7.9 released","url":"https://www.openbsd.org/79.html","score":56,"flags":0,"comment_count":6,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"utzig","user_is_author":false,"tags":["openbsd","release"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/wwcjoc","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/wwcjoc/openbsd_7_9_released"},{"short_id":"prer9l","created_at":"2026-05-19T07:53:39.000-05:00","title":"Software's Centaur Era","url":"https://twitchard.github.io/posts/2026-05-18-softwares-centaur-era.html","score":12,"flags":1,"comment_count":5,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"carlana","user_is_author":false,"tags":["vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/prer9l","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/prer9l/software_s_centaur_era"},{"short_id":"zsjasr","created_at":"2026-05-19T07:29:28.000-05:00","title":"My domain got abused on Github Pages","url":"https://meertens.dev/blog/github-enables-domain-abuse/","score":26,"flags":0,"comment_count":5,"description":"","description